I know there are plenty of things people wish they never invented/discovered after the fact ans many of the chemical weapons used/created are like that...nuclear bombs are the same...biological, hey aren&#39;t those bugs deadly enough without you fiddling with them.  I&#39;d say they&#39;re the stupidist of all as they can mutate on their own so even if you think your country/army are safe with the vaccine you&#39;ve made up against your tailor-made biological weapon they may not be given a couple of generations of mutation to the bacteria or virus... </TD></TR><TR><td width='4' valign='top' bgcolor=#CCCCCC>*</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#CCCCCC><font class="bfont"><B>Dredlox™</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#CCCCCC><font class="bfont">Could you clarify?  Do you mean if a "country uses chemical, biological, or nuclear weapons of mass destruction" anywhere or just against us? </TD></TR><TR><td width='4' valign='top' bgcolor=#FFFFFF>*</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>The Judge™</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont">The United States is posting a statement to congress that if any hostile country uses chemical, biological, or nuclear weapons of mass destruction, that we will retaliate with nuclear weapons.<br />
